@node "BumpRevision" "rexx_icon.library/BumpRevision"

BumpRevision :


    NAME

        BumpRevision -- Reformat a name for a second copy.

    SYNOPSIS

        newname = BumpRevision(oldname)

    FUNCTION

        BumpRevision takes a name and turns it into a "copy_of_name". It
        knows how to deal with copies of copies. The routine will truncate
        the new name to the maximum dos name size (currently 30 chars).

    INPUTS

        oldname - The original name (normally a file name without path).
                  It must be at least 30 chars long.

    RESULT

        A new name like the following (oldname newname):

        "foo"                            "copy_of_foo"
        "copy_of_foo"                    "copy_2_of_foo"
        "copy_2_of_foo"                  "copy_3_of_foo"
        "copy_199_of_foo"                "copy_200_of_foo"
        "copy foo"                       "copy_of_copy foo"
        "copy_0_of_foo"                  "copy_1_of_foo"
        "012345678901234567890123456789" "copy_of_0123456789012345678901"

    EXAMPLE

        SAY BumpRevision("tempfile")

    SEE ALSO

        icon.library/BumpRevision()

@endnode
@node "DeleteDiskObj" "rexx_icon.library/DeleteDiskObj"

DeleteDiskObj :


    NAME

        DeleteDiskObj -- Delete a Workbench disk object from disk.

    SYNOPSIS

        success = DeleteDiskObj(iconpath)

    FUNCTION

        This routine will try to delete a Workbench disk object from disk.
        The name parameter will have a ".info" postpended to it, and the
        info file of that name will be deleted. If the call fails, it will
        return zero. This call also updates the Workbench screen if needed.

    INPUTS

        iconpath - The path name of the icon (without ".info").

    RESULT

        success - boolean value (1 mean all done, ok).

    EXAMPLE

        CALL DeleteDiskObj("RAM:t")     /* Delete "RAM:t.info" */

    SEE ALSO

        icon.library/DeleteDiskObject()

@endnode
@node "GetDiskObj" "rexx_icon.library/GetDiskObj"

GetDiskObj :


    NAME

        GetDiskObj -- Read in a Workbench disk object from disk.

    SYNOPSIS

        type = GetDiskObj(iconpath,options)

    FUNCTION

        This routine reads in a Workbench disk object from disk. The name
        parameter will have a ".info" postpended to it, and the info file
        of that name will be read.

    INPUTS

        iconpath - The path name of the icon (without ".info").

        options  - "Outstem/A"

            "Outstem" - The output stem must be specified. It will
                        receive all data readed from the given info
                        file. The stem variable consists of the
                        following fields:

                            <stem.>Type
                                An integer number representing the type
                                of the icon:

                                    WBDISK      1
                                    WBDRAWER    2
                                    WBTOOL      3
                                    WBPROJECT   4
                                    WBGARBAGE   5
                                    WBDEVICE    6
                                    WBKICK      7
                                    WBAPPICON   8

                            <stem.>PosX
                            <stem.>PosY
                                The position of every icon is relative
                                to an origin defined into each drawer.

                            <stem.>Stack
                                The stack size is defined only for
                                WBTOOL or WBPROJECT icons.

                            <stem.>DefTool
                                The default tool is defined only for
                                WBPROJECT and WBDISK icons.

                            <stem.>n
                                The tooltypes array.

                        This function supports "#" and "*" stems types
                        (read the rexxMOOS documentation for details).

    RESULT

        The function returns a number representing the icon type (as
        defined above) or 0 in case of failures.

    EXAMPLE

        SAY GetDiskObj("tempfile")

    SEE ALSO

        icon.library/GetDiskObject()

@endnode
@node "PutDiskObj" "rexx_icon.library/PutDiskObj"

PutDiskObj :


    NAME

        PutDiskObj -- Write out a DiskObject to disk.

    SYNOPSIS

        success = PutDiskObj(desticon,sourceicon,options)

    FUNCTION

        This routine writes out a DiskObject structure, and its associated
        information. The file name of the info file will be the name
        parameter with a ".info" postpended to it.

    INPUTS

        desticon   - Destination icon's path, without ".info".

        sourceicon - A source icon can be specified and with the options
                     keywords is possible to select which parts are to be
                     copied into the destination.

        options    - "Images/S,Type/K/N,PosX/S,PosY/S,
                      DefTool/S,Stack/S,TT/S"

            "Images"  - 
            "Type"    - 
            "PosX"    - 
            "PosY"    - 
            "DefTool" - 
            "Stack"   - 
            "TT"      - 

    RESULT

        success - boolean value (1 mean all done, ok).

    EXAMPLE

        SAY PutDiskObj("tempfile")

    NOTES

        A file associated with the destination icon must exists.

    SEE ALSO

        icon.library/PutDiskObject()

@endnode
@node "SetDiskObj" "rexx_icon.library/SetDiskObj"

SetDiskObj :


    NAME

        SetDiskObj -- Change data into a Workbench disk object.

    SYNOPSIS

        success = SetDiskObj(iconpath,options)

    FUNCTION

        This routine can change the attributes of a Workbench disk object.
        The name parameter will have a ".info" postpended to it and the
        info file of that name will be used.

    INPUTS

        iconpath - The path name of the icon (without ".info").

        options  - "Type/K/N,PosX/K/N,PosY/K/N,DefTool/K,Stack/K/N,
                    Instem,TT/K"

            "Type"    - An integer number representing icon's type:

                            WBDISK      1
                            WBDRAWER    2
                            WBTOOL      3
                            WBPROJECT   4
                            WBGARBAGE   5
                            WBKICK      7

            "PosX"    - The position of every icon is relative to an
            "PosY"    - origin defined into each drawer.

            "DefTool" - The default tool is defined only for WBPROJECT
                        and WBDISK icons.

            Stack"    - The stack size is defined only for WBTOOL or
                        WBPROJECT icons.

            "Instem"  - Icon's attribute can be specified also into an
                        input stem (see rexx_icon.library/GetDiskObj()
                        for its structure):

                            <stem.>Type
                            <stem.>PosX
                            <stem.>PosY
                            <stem.>Stack
                            <stem.>DefTool

                            <stem.>n
                                The tooltypes array.

                        Both "#" and "*" stems types are supported
                        (read the rexxMOOS documentation for details).
                        This input stem can be used in conjunction with
                        other keywords and, in this case, corresponding
                        values into the stem are ignored.

            "TT"      - Instead of using the tooltypes defined into the
                        "Instem" structure, an alternative stem can be
                        specified using this keyword.

    RESULT

        success - boolean value (1 mean all done, ok).

    EXAMPLE

        SAY SetDiskObj("tempfile",'DefTool "c:iconx"')

    SEE ALSO

        icon.library/PutDiskObject()

@endnode

